# UML Class Diagram
  ```mermaid
  classDiagram
      class IdWorker{
          +long generateId()
          +long getLastGeneratedId()
      }
      class SidWorker{
          +long generateId()
      }
      class Base62{
          +String encode(long id)
          +long decode(String encodedId)
      }
      class Main{
          +void generateIds(int numIds, String outputFile)
      }
      IdWorker "1" -- "*" SidWorker: generates
      IdWorker "1" -- "*" Base62: encodes
      SidWorker "1" -- "*" Base62: encodes
      Main "1" -- "*" IdWorker: generates
      Main "1" -- "*" SidWorker: generates
  ```
  This UML class diagram represents the classes and their relationships as per the requirements of the Product Requirement Document (PRD). The classes are IdWorker, SidWorker, Base62, and Main. The IdWorker class is responsible for generating unique IDs, SidWorker for timestamp-based IDs, and Base62 for encoding and decoding. The Main class is the entry point for the application and generates IDs based on the parameters provided. The relationships between the classes are represented by the dashed lines.

